description: {"blocks":[{"key":"99dm5","text":"This protocol provides detailed methods for in-field collection of grain yield data using a combine harvester equipped with a yield monitor. Proper in-field procedures are key to the collection of high-quality continuous grain yield data. Well-functioning harvest equipment including the combine, yield monitor, and sensors are necessary to produce high-quality data. These data are exported via USB or cloud transfer and a yield map can be developed. Yield maps are highly valuable for farmers and scientists as we work towards increased production and yield stability. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"447au","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"81fed","text":"To reduce error and provide high-quality continuous grain yield data we recommend the following steps: harvester setup and calibration, field overview, machine operation (yield monitor setup, calibration, set export parameters), and applying calibration. These will be discussed in detailed sections below. A separate protocol (USDA LTAR Common Experiment measurement: Post-processing of spatial grain yield data) addresses the post-processing steps required to convert yield data into accurate yield maps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":328,"length":84}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1r6rj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"buk5i","text":"Across the LTAR Cropland Experiments to-date, there are four sites that utilize John Deere Greenstar yield monitors while eight utilize Ag Leader Integra yield monitors (based on a survey in 2022). In this protocol, we focus primarily on Ag Leader Integra procedures and recommendations due to its prevalence among the sites but also provide information regarding the John Deere Greenstar system. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3p1d9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"47srj","text":"We suggest utilizing the Ag Leader monitoring system to obtain research-grade data when possible. We understand the cost and familiarity issues associated with moving to a new system. However, after 2012, the John Deere Greenstar system was replaced by Greenstar ActiveYield. Using ActiveYield can create more difficulty during the post-processing phase. This is due to the calibration adjustments which occur automatically when using ActiveYield, which may result in many different calibration curves within a single field. Application of these calibration curves occurs only for the section of the field that has just been calibrated, essentially creating multiple data sets for a single field. Therefore, if using the post-2012 Greenstar system we recommend disabling ActiveYield and using the manual, multi-point calibration procedure to make post-processing more repeatable and clearer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3820s","text":"Before harvesting, update any monitor software to the newest version available and review your combine manual to ensure the combine is serviced and working properly. Details about maintenance, setup, calibration, and operation can be found there.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2f4jj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9r10g","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"em9f2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"2iasb","text":"Yearly checks of harvesting machinery, sensors, and yield monitors are essential to avoid problems such as unresponsive sensors and general combine breakdowns which can be a result of poor pre-harvest inspection.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"74bim","text":"It is also important to check the version of the yield monitor operating software and install the newest version. See Figure 1 for a diagram showing the general location of sensors in a typical combine yield monitoring system. {"blocks":[{"key":"ckhu7","text":"First, a visual inspection of the combine and its components should be performed to ensure there is no damage and the machine is in good working condition. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7jej","text":"Inspect the sensors and wiring based on the following steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ona5","text":"Check for damage to the mass flow, grain moisture, elevator speed, and header position sensors. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"35p5k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"au4b2","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"15vk8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"evv7t","text":"In most yield monitoring systems, the mass flow sensor is an impact plate against which grain is thrown from the top of the clean grain elevator. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ao1bg","text":"Be sure your sensors have not shifted in position and are firmly attached. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fk6v2","text":"Check your impact plate for debris and damage such as holes, divots, and cracks.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d5nbd","text":"Also check the area behind the plate for material buildup and make sure the clearance between the impact plate and elevator paddles is within specification.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4b8v1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ium4","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fhr9s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4b5rv","text":"If using an Ag Leader Integra yield monitor, the manual states that clearance between the elevator paddles and the plate should be between 3/8 and 5/8 inch. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ddi5q","text":"In particular, ensure the elevator chain is tight and the paddles are not extremely worn.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53bg6","text":"The combine may require sensor calibration especially if it is new or has new parts such as a new head or impact plate flow sensor. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"56tlv","text":"Once again, consult the brand-specific manual for the harvester and yield monitor to set up and calibrate your combine properly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ti75","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3cri1","text":"In addition, perform a test harvest on a small section of the field or nearby “bulk” area to verify the system is running properly. A detailed section on completing a test harvest is below. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bkp3r","text":"Before harvesting a field, make yourself aware of possible impediments to harvesting such as in-field features (ditch, terracing), obstacles (old well, rocks), and crop damage (weak stalks due to insect feeding).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"12ehm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7d3a4","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"bo5mf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"eq18n","text":"By having this knowledge, potential damage to the combine is avoided, there is time to ask questions before entering the field, and a mental plan can be developed for how to best harvest the field to account for obstacles.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2pfij","text":"Also investigate potential challenges that may affect your harvest plan, such as severely lodged corn which may require harvesting in only one direction to allow the combine head to pick up the stalks.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eaklc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2nu2n","text":"A yield monitor is required for collection of yield data during harvest. Place the monitor so you have easy access to the screen for viewing and adjustments while driving the combine. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f26kb","text":"Avoid placing the monitor where it hinders access to machine controls, or your view.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"o7am","text":"All wiring should be placed in a manner such that it does not cause a tripping hazard.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ft26k","text":"Before installing the yield monitor, check the wires for damage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5i8m8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1btes","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2q8v6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7k1o3","text":"For more specifics, see the instructions in your installation and mounting kit and brand-specific yield monitor manual.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e71ll","text":"When using the yield monitor for the first time, you will need to specify the required settings when prompted during setup.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bj7lv","text":"Systems may allow choice of metric (SI) or conventional (or Imperial) units. Imperial units will often be preferred as that is most familiar to the majority of combine operators. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fo6o5","text":"In addition, the operator should check that appropriate field metadata are chosen or entered in the monitor before starting the field of interest.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1001q","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8qbie","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"70sfi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"budil","text":"Metadata includes farm and field names, crop type, hybrid or variety, and other identifying information.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"s5b2","text":"It is important to enter proper machine measurements, which will ensure accurate offset values.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dk09s","text":"A general harvest suggestion for producing high quality data is the creation of good harvest patterns which avoid operational errors. steps.section: Ag Leader and John Deere calibrations compared
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4mkmf","text":"It is IMPORTANT to understand how calibration works for your yield monitor. Ag Leader monitors apply calibration to all fields of the same year and crop type which makes data uniform. John Deere calibration is not applied backward to previously harvested data for that crop type and year. As indicated in weight calibration above, this means a new data set will essentially be created within the field each time a new calibration is performed in the field. For all yield monitors, the best practice is to collect data to develop an accurate calibration before harvesting any fields or plots where yield data will be used for research purposes.
